employees and community citizens especially as farleys promises to modernize and expand the company never came to fruition less than four years later the company filed bankruptcy and farley resigned to focus his efforts on fruit of the loom  fruit of the loom would ultimately declare bankruptcy in  farley walked away from that company as well fruit of the loomedit though farley eventually sold most businesses within the farleynorthwest holding corp conglomerate he kept fruit of the loom inc in march  farley completed a successful  million public offering of fruit of the loom shares farley served as president and ceo of fruit of the loom from  to  during that time fruit of the looms revenue grew from  million to almost  billion at its peak farley industries employed over  employees worldwide during his tenure as president and ceo of fruit of the loom revenues rose nearly fivefold from  million to almost  billion at its peak in  fruit of the loom was trading at roughly  per share the press teased farley about the companys unconventional advertisements featuring farley even while the companys revenue was rising sharply its debt proved increasingly unwieldy amid the shifting economy in  fruit of the loom posted a net loss of  million and the company filed for bankruptcy farley left fruit of the loom that same year in  fruit of the loom was purchased by berkshire hathaway the fruit of the loom bankruptcy was farleys third in  years preceded by the failures under his leadership of farley industries and west point pepperell junk bond failuresedit while farleys success in the s had made him wealthy his junkbond processes failed miserably in the s ultimately leading to bankruptcy for several companies he had attempted to take over  zrii llcedit in may  farley launched a brandnew multilevel marketing health and beauty company based out of salt lake city utah the company zrii llc had more than  independent distributors attend its launch at the salt lake city convention center zrii a sanskrit word which means light luster splendor and prosperity was endorsed by lifestyle guru deepak chopra and the chopra center for wellbeing the basis of its namesake product was a juice extracted from the amalaki fruit which is grown exclusively in india at the base of the himalayas in february   employees staged a walkout of zrii headquarters and demanded that farley resigncitation needed the employees had formed their own company and attempted to make an offer to take over zrii but farley refused to step down he sued the top managers claiming that their goal was to force him out in order to purchase the company for a reduced cost the lawsuit further claimed that the employees had deliberately raided and sabotaged company computers before the walkout in december  farley won  in a settlement agreement with lifevantage corporation where many of his former employees were hired lifevantage admitted no interference with zriis operations in the settlement agreement management styleedit farley spent over  million a year on programs at his subsidiaries that encouraged physical fitness good nutrition and smoking cessation he traveled to work sites and solicited employees opinions about the quality of their food and facilities making improvements if his workers werent satisfied farley installed baseball fields tracks and other fitness facilities at plants and factories farley was also known for his relentless work ethic and his schedule often demanded brutal hours he occasionally held meetings with managers late at night if there was no available time during the day farley also preferred to keep his companies small and efficiently organized he is known for insisting that company hierarchies be trimmed down to reduce the number of layers between the lowestlevel workers and toplevel executives philanthropic activityedit a firm believer in education farley has contributed millions of dollars to his alma maters his largest single contribution was a  million gift to bowdoin college in  which resulted in farley field house an indoor athletic facility with a track indoor tennis courts and spectator areas he also founded scholarship programs for students at boston college law school and made a  million donation to endow the william f farley chair at the law school in may  farley made a  million donation to his high school st raphael academy which went toward science and computer resources tuition assistance and the athletic department in  and in honor of farleys contributions to the school the west annex building at st raphael was renamed barbara farley hall in honor of farleys mother farley has made numerous contributions over the years to the american heart association and hes been a donor to and board member of various civic and cultural organizations in his adopted hometown of chicago illinois including the goodman theater the lyric opera house and the chicago council on foreign relations he has also sat on the board of directors for the horatio alger association awards and honorsedit  farley is recognized as outstanding business graduate of the year by the boston college law school alumni association  farley receives the horatio alger association of distinguished americans award the award is given to community leaders who demonstrate individual initiative and a commitment to excellence as exemplified by remarkable achievements accomplished through honesty hard work selfreliance and perseverance over adversity  farley is inducted into the rhode island heritage hall of fame and is honored by the boys  girls club of america as a businesscommunity honoree of the year  honored by the irelandus council for commerce and industry for outstanding achievement for his work in economics business and commercial activity he also is named one of irishamerica magazines top  businessmen and receives the white houses presidential award for entrepreneurial excellence  farley is honored with a freedom award from americas freedom festival at provo personal lifeedit farley was a high school athlete at st raphael academy in pawtucket rhode island and played three varsity sports football swimming and baseball at bowdoin he provided financial support to the athletic departments at st raphael and bowdoin in the s farley became a minority owner of the chicago white sox farley was an active member in the young presidents organization he is currently a member of the world presidents organization he has also been a member of the chicago club and the university associates of northwestern university for years farley lives in chicago with his wife shelley a cabaret singer who has performed michael feinstein george burns and president bill clinton farley has three sons the youngest liam lives in chicago with him his two older sons hayes macarthur and scott live in los angeles referencesedit  a b c d labich kenneth may   bill farley has a dream machine fortune  a b c d e f g chiappinelli bob july   pawtuckets horatio alger providence sunday journal  a b klein amy may   schools benefactor renames building for his mother the providence journalbulletin  a b c d sheridan mike april  profile william f farley echelon magazine  a b c bill farley casts a wide net for companies financial enterprise summer   herguth bob january   chicago profile william f farley chicago suntimes  sheridan mike april  profile william f farley echelon magazine  a b c cs january   the buyout man us news  world report  farleynorthwest to sell subsidiary tribunedigitalchicagotribune retrieved    northwest industries wwwnndbcom retrieved    a major deal maker of the s is drowning in debt in the s los angeles times retrieved   check date values in accessdate help  west point pepperell buyer steps down as its chairman new york times retrieved    fruit of loom back as farley makes changes tribunedigitalchicagotribune retrieved    bill farley the handson conglomerator industry week june    a b c d e delaney patricia  farley chair in legal studies endowed boston college chronicle   harvey tom february   utah drink firm in meltdown the salt lake tribune  harvey tom february   utah drink firm in meltdown the salt lake tribune  a major deal maker of the s is drowning in debt in the s los angeles times retrieved   check date values in accessdate help  harvey tom may   draper company launches zrii says its a healthful juice the salt lake tribune  harvey tom december   supplement company zrii settles suits against rebellious exmanagers the salt lake tribune  bill farley the handson conglomerator industry week june    a b brayton steve january   kindness to workers farleys key to success the boston herald  a b farley honored with horatio alger award bowdoin orient   bowdoin athletics  william farley field house athleticsbowdoinedu retrieved    alumni give back to sra the pawtucket times   about us horatio alger retrieved    rhode island heritage hall of fame inductees from  riheritagehalloffameorg retrieved     delaney patricia  farley chair in legal studies endowed boston college chronicle  davis james july   festival salutes  heroes deseret news  qa with shelley macarthur auditorium theatre retrieved   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlewilliamffarleyoldid categories  birthsliving peopleamerican retail chief executivesbusinesspeople from rhode islandamerican philanthropistsboston college alumnihidden categories cs errors datesall articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from june  navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version l