y industries  west point pepperell  fruit of the loom  junk bond failures  zrii llc  management style  philanthropic activity  awards and honors  personal life  references biographyedit early life and educationedit farley was born the elder of two children to a workingclass irish catholic family on october   in pawtucket rhode island he was the son of john farley a postal worker and parttime musician and barbara farley a receptionist farley attended grade school at st leos school in pawtucket and later became a recruited high school athlete and student at st raphael academy his fathers high school farley graduated from st raphaels in  farley attended bowdoin college in brunswick maine from – where he majored in government and earned an academic scholarship at bowdoin he was a varsity athlete in football swimming and baseball he received a juris doctorate from boston college in  professional careeredit early yearsedit after graduating from bowdoin in  farley traveled across the us and mexico for six months eventually settling in los angeles in los angeles farley sold colliers encyclopedia door to door within two years he was the companys leading salesman and was appointed head of training for the national sales force farley entered the boston college law school in  earning a jd in  nl industries and lehman brothersedit after law school farley moved to new york city where he took a job in the mergers and acquisitions division of nl industries a manufacturing company with a number of subsidiaries at nl industries farley did analysis on potential acquisition targets and rose to director of long range planning and acquisitions during this time he pursued an mba at new york university in  farley was transferred to chicago where he functioned as the regional manager of nl industries metals division in  farley left nl industries and took a position as an associate in the corporate finance division of lehman brothers in chicago farley industriesedit in  nl industries contacted farley at lehman brothers to see if he knew of a potential buyer for anaheim citrus products co a small subsidiary that produced pectin a thickening agent used in foods and other products in october  at age  he executed his first leveraged buyout for  million to facilitate the buyout farley founded farley industries a private holdings company in the sears tower in chicago after six months farley had raised the funds for the buyout including his life savings of  plus  million in loans and notes borrowed against the company assets within two years after the buyout anaheim citrus had doubled its sales in  farley purchased baumfolder corporation a struggling manufacturing company using funds from equipment sales at anaheim citrus farley quit lehman and moved to ohio to oversee the baumfolder turnaround he later sold baumfolder to its employees for  million in  farley purchased nl metals the same group he used to run at nl the purchase price was  million making nl metals the first in a line of significantly larger acquisitions that farley would make over the next decade farley industries soon encompassed numerous companies within the manufacturing mining and apparel industries the largest acquisition was northwest industries for  billion in july  farley industries had  employees and nearly  billion in annual sales by the late s in  farley industries entered bankruptcy and was dismantled west point pepperelledit in  farley completed a hostile takeover of west point pepperell inc a textile company that had been familyowned in west point georgia and surrounding communities for more than  years farley paid  billion for the company eclipsing the mark of  billion he had paid a year prior for northwest industries farley financed his purchase of  percent of the company through bank debt and highyield junk bonds the hostile takeover did not sit well with employees and community citizens especially as farleys promises to modernize and expand the company never came to fruition less than four years later the company filed bankruptcy and farley resigned to focus his efforts on fruit of the loom  fruit of the loom would ultimately declare bankruptcy in  farley walked away from that company as well fruit of the loomedit though farley eventually sold most businesses within the farleynorthwest holding corp conglomerate he kept fruit of the loom inc in march  farley completed a successful  million public offering of fruit of the loom shares farley served as president and ceo of fruit of the loom from  to  during that time fruit of the looms revenue grew from  million to almost  billion at its peak farley industries employed over  employees worldwide during his tenure as president and ceo of fruit of the loom revenues rose nearly fivefold from  million to almost  billion at its peak in  fruit of the loom was trading at roughly  per share the press teased farley about the companys unconventional advertisements featuring farley even while the companys revenue was rising sharply its debt proved increasingly unwieldy amid the shifting economy in  fruit of the loom posted a net loss of  million and the company filed for bankruptcy farley left fruit of the loom that same year in  fruit of the loom was purchased by berkshire hathaway the fruit of the loom bankruptcy was farleys third in  years preceded by the failures under his leadership of farley industries and west point pepperell junk bond failuresedit while farleys success in the s had made him wealthy his junkbond processes failed miserably in the s ultimately leading to bankruptcy for several companies he had attempted to take over  zrii llcedit in may  farley launched a brandnew multilevel marketing health and beauty company based out of salt lake city utah the company zrii llc had more than  independent distributors attend its launch at the salt lake city convention center zrii a sanskrit word which means light luster splendor and prosperity was endorsed by lifestyle guru deepak chopra and the chopra center for wellbeing the basis of its namesake product was a juice extracted from the amalaki fruit which is grown exclusively in india at the base of the himalayas in february   employees staged a walkout of zrii headquarters and demanded that farley resigncitation needed the employees had formed their own company and attempted to make an offer to take over zrii but farley refused to step down he sued the top managers claiming that their goal was to force him out in order to purchase the company for a reduced cost the lawsuit further claimed that the employees had deliberately raided and sabotaged company computers before the walkout in december  farley won  in a settlement agreement with lifevantage corporation where many of his former employees were hired lifevantage admitted no interference with zriis operations in the settlement agreement management styleedit farley spent over  million a year on programs at his subsidiaries that encouraged physical fitness good nutrition and smoking cessation he traveled to work sites and solicited employees opinions about the quality of their food and facilities making improvements if his workers werent satisfied farley installed baseball fields tracks and other fitness facilities at plants and factories farley was also known for his relentless work ethic and his schedule often demanded brutal hours he occasionally held meetings with managers late at night if there was no available time during the day farley also preferred to keep his companies small and efficiently organized he is known for insisting that company hierarchies be trimmed down to reduce the number of layers between the lowestlevel workers and toplevel executives philanthropic activityedit a firm believer in education farley has contributed millions of dollars to his alma maters his largest single contribution was a  million gift to bowdoin college in  which resulted in farley field house an indoor athletic facility with a track indoor tennis courts and spectator areas he also founded scholarship programs for students at boston college law school and made a  million donation to endow the william f farley chair at the law school in may  farley made a  million donation to his high school st raphael academy which went toward science and computer resources tuition assistance and the athletic department in  and in honor of farleys contributions to the school the west annex building at st raphael was renamed barbara farley hall in honor of farleys mother farley has made numerous contributions over the years to the american heart association and hes been a donor to and board member of various civic and cultural organizations in his adopted hometown of chicago illinois including the goodman theater the lyric opera house and the chicago council on foreign relations he has also sat on the board of directors for the horatio alger association awards and honorsedit  farley is recognized as outstanding business graduate of the year by the boston college law school alumni association  farley receives the horatio alger association of distinguished americans award the award is given to community leaders who demonstrate individual initiative and a commitment to excellence as exemplified by remarkable achievements accomplished through honesty hard work selfreliance and perseverance over adversity  farley is inducted into the rhode island heritage hall of fame and is honored by the boys  girls club of america as a businesscommunity honoree of the year  honored by the irelandus council for commerce and industry for outstanding achievement for his work in economics business and commercial activity he also is named one of irishamerica magazines top  businessmen and receives the white houses presidential award for entrepreneurial excellence  farley is honored with a freedom award from americas freedom festival at provo personal lifeedit farley was a high school athlete at st raphael academy in pawtucket rhode island and played three varsity sports football swimming and baseball at bowdoin he provided financial support to the athletic departments at st raphael and bowdoin in the s farley became a minority owner of the chicago white sox farley was an active member in the young presidents organization he is currently a member of the world presidents organization he has also been a member of the chicago club and the university associates of northwestern university for years farley lives in chicago with his wife shelley a cabaret singer who has performed michael feinstein george burns and president bill clinton farley has three sons the youngest liam lives in chicago with him his two older sons hayes macarthur and scott live in los angeles referencesedit  a b c d labich kenneth may   bill farley has a dream machine fortune  a b c d e f g chiappinelli bob july   pawtuckets horatio alger providence sunday journal  a b klein amy may   schools benefactor renames building for his mother the providence journalbulletin  a b c d sheridan mike april  profile william f farley echelon magazine  a b c bill farley casts a wide net for companies financial enterprise summer   herguth bob january   chicago profile william f farley chicago suntimes  sheridan mike april  profile william f farley echelon magazine  a b c cs january   the buyout man us news  world report  farleynorthwest to sell subsidiary tribunedigitalchicagotribune retrieved    northwest industries wwwnndbcom retrieved    a major deal maker of the s is drowning in debt in the s los angeles times retrieved   check date values in accessdate help  west point pepperell buyer steps down as its chairman new york times retrieved    fruit of loom back as farley makes changes tribunedigitalchicagotribune retrieved    bill farley the handson conglomerator industry week june    a b c d e delaney patricia  farley chair in legal studies endowed boston college chronicle   harvey tom february   utah drink firm in meltdown the salt lake tribune  harvey tom february   utah d